http://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/TZ-Variable.html
https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Time#Time_zone

TZ=":/etc/localtime" #=> use the system local time (this is the default when TZ is unset)
This is the best, I can use timedatectl to change both the system and user
timezone at the same time!

Specific user settings: timedatectl $TZ
TZ="Europe/Paris"
TZ="Europe/Dublin"
TZ="America/Edmonton"
TZ="Pacific/Honolulu"
TZ="Europe/Moscow"
TZ="America/Los_Angeles"
TZ="Africa/Casablanca"
TZ="Pacific/Tahiti"
TZ="Asia/Seoul"
TZ="Asia/Calcutta"
TZ="America/Costa_Rica"
TZ="Africa/Libreville "
TZ="Africa/Dakar"
TZ="Europe/Lisbon"
